---
title: Cajun Spice-Rubbed Pork with Bulgur Wheat, Garlicky Savoy Cabbage and Tomato Sauce
description: Making bulgur from wheat is one of the oldest food processes in the world - some say it’s over 4,000 years old. When something’s been around for that long, you know it must be pretty solid. Add that to rich, deep Cajun pork and some simple garlicky greens and you’ve got yourself a bit of a feast!
